      • getAction

        public java.util.List<Action> getAction()
        Gets the value of the action property. This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the action property. For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 
         getAction().add(newItem);
        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list Action
        Returns:
        the value of the action property.
